cs.HC, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.DS 

The paper deals with optimization in collaborative crowdsourcing, which involves human-based computing and social factors. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The paper also proposes a model and algorithms for optimization, which falls under the scope of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The social factors and theories used in the formalism suggest that the paper could also be classified under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CY (Computers and Society). Finally, the paper involves theoretical analyses and algorithmic design, which could be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
